Requirement
------------

python
python-pika


Description
-----------

Send remote command to a server via AMQP bus. I used this to make some automation with AWS autoscaling and puppet.


Install
-------

Debian way: Just build the package, debuild...

To install the listening daemon: dpkg --install rpcmq-server
To install the client: dpkg --install rpcmq-client

The old way: 
create /etc/rpcmq /opt/rpcmq
copy etc/* /etc/rpcmq/
copy bin sbin to /opt/rpcmq/
copy rpc-scripts to /opt

PS: AMQPS is currently broken in pika library, should be available in next version (0.9.6)
